395 GPS_STATUS_FIX_NONE = (int)0x00000000,

398 GPS_STATUS_FIX_3D = (int)0x00000300,
399 GPS_STATUS_FIX_GPS_PLUS_DEAD_RECK = (int)0x00000400,
400 GPS_STATUS_FIX_TIME_ONLY = (int)0x00000500,
401 GPS_STATUS_FIX_UNUSED1 = (int)0x00000600,
402 GPS_STATUS_FIX_UNUSED2 = (int)0x00000700,
403 GPS_STATUS_FIX_DGPS = (int)0x00000800,
404 GPS_STATUS_FIX_SBAS = (int)0x00000900,
405 GPS_STATUS_FIX_RTK_SINGLE = (int)0x00000A00,
406 GPS_STATUS_FIX_RTK_FLOAT = (int)0x00000B00,
407 GPS_STATUS_FIX_RTK_FIX = (int)0x00000C00,
408 GPS_STATUS_FIX_MASK = (int)0x00001F00,
409 GPS_STATUS_FIX_BIT_OFFSET = (int)8,
410
412 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_FIX_OK = (int)0x00010000, // within limits (e.g. DOP & accuracy)
413 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_DGPS_USED = (int)0x00020000, // Differential GPS (DGPS) used.
414 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_FIX_AND_HOLD = (int)0x00040000, // RTK feedback on the integer solutions to drive the float biases towards the resolved integers
415// GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_WEEK_VALID = (int)0x00040000,
416// GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_TOW_VALID = (int)0x00080000,
417 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_POSITION_ENABLED = (int)0x00100000, // RTK precision positioning mode enabled
418 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_STATIC_MODE = (int)0x00200000, // Static mode
419 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_ENABLED = (int)0x00400000, // RTK moving base mode enabled
420 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_RAW_GPS_DATA_ERROR = (int)0x00800000, // RTK error: observations or ephemeris are invalid or not received (i.e. RTK differential corrections)
421 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_BASE_DATA_MISSING = (int)0x01000000, // RTK error: Either base observations or antenna position have not been received.
422 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_BASE_POSITION_MOVING = (int)0x02000000, // RTK error: base position moved when it should be stationary
423 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_BASE_POSITION_INVALID = (int)0x03000000, // RTK error: base position is invalid or not surveyed well
424 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_BASE_POSITION_MASK = (int)0x03000000, // RTK error: base position error bitmask
425 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_ERROR_MASK = (GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_RAW_GPS_DATA_ERROR|
426 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_BASE_POSITION_MASK),
427 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_POSITION_VALID = (int)0x04000000, // GPS1 RTK precision position and carrier phase range solution with fixed ambiguities (i.e. < 6cm horizontal accuracy). The carrier phase range solution with floating ambiguities occurs if GPS_STATUS_FIX_RTK_FIX is set and GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_POSITION_VALID is not set (i.e. > 6cm horizontal accuracy).
428 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_VALID = (int)0x08000000, // GPS2 RTK moving base heading. Indicates RTK fix and hold with single band RTK compassing.
429 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_BASELINE_BAD = (int)0x00002000,
430 GPS_STATUS_FLAGS_RTK_COMPASSING_BASELINE_UNSET = (int)0x00004000,

1619enum eBitState
1620{
1621 BIT_STATE_OFF = (int)0,
1622 BIT_STATE_DONE = (int)1, // Test is finished
1623 BIT_STATE_CMD_FULL_STATIONARY = (int)2, // (FULL) Comprehensive test. Requires system be completely stationary without vibrations.
1624 BIT_STATE_CMD_BASIC_MOVING = (int)3, // (BASIC) Ignores sensor output. Can be run while moving. This mode is automatically run after bootup.
1625 BIT_STATE_CMD_FULL_STATIONARY_HIGH_ACCURACY = (int)4, // Same as BIT_STATE_CMD_FULL_STATIONARY but with higher requirements for accuracy. In order to pass, this test may require the Infield Calibration (DID_INFIELD_CAL) to be run.

1746 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_INIT_OPTION_DISABLE_REQUIRE_VERTIAL = 0x00020000, // Bitwise AND this with the above init commands to disable vertical alignment requirement for accelerometer bias calibration (allow for more tolerant sampling).
1747
1749 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_START_SAMPLE = 8, // Initiate 5 second sensor sampling and averaging. Run for each orientation and 180 degree yaw rotation.
1750 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_SAVE_AND_FINISH = 9, // Run this command to compute and save results. Must be run following INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_START_SAMPLE.
1751
1753 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_READY_FOR_SAMPLING = 50, // System has been initialized and is waiting for user to intiate sampling. User must send a command to exit this state.
1754 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_SAMPLING = 51, // System is averaging the IMU data. Minimize all motion and vibration.
1755 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_RUN_BIT_AND_FINISH = 52, // Follow up calibration zero with BIT and copy out IMU biases.
1756 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_SAVED_AND_FINISHED = 53, // Calculations are complete and DID_INFIELD_CAL.imu holds the update IMU biases. Updates are saved to flash.
1757
1759 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_ERROR_NOT_INITIALIZED = 100, // Init command (INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_INIT_...) not set.
1760 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_ERROR_SAMPLE_ABORT_MOTION_DETECTED= 101, // Error: Motion detected. Sampling aborted.
1761 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_ERROR_SAMPLE_ABORT_NOT_VERTICAL = 102, // Error: System not vertical. Sampling aborted.
1762 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_ERROR_NO_SAMPLES_COLLECTED = 103, // Error: No samples have been collected
1763 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_ERROR_POOR_CAL_FIT = 104, // Error: Calibration zero is not
1764
1766 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_MASK = 0x0000FFFF,
1767 INFIELD_CAL_STATE_CMD_START_SAMPLE_BIT = 11, // Initiate 5 second sensor sample and averaging. Does not save sample into cal data.
1768};

4228// BE_SWAP: if big endian then swap, else no-op
4229// LE_SWAP: if little endian then swap, else no-op
4230#if CPU_IS_BIG_ENDIAN
4231#define BE_SWAP64F(_i) flipDoubleCopy(_i)
4232#define BE_SWAP32F(_i) flipFloatCopy(_i)
4233#define BE_SWAP32(_i) (SWAP32(_i))
4234#define BE_SWAP16(_i) (SWAP16(_i))
4235#define LE_SWAP64F(_i) (_i)
4236#define LE_SWAP32F(_i) (_i)
4237#define LE_SWAP32(_i) (_i)
4238#define LE_SWAP16(_i) (_i)
4239#else // little endian
4240#define BE_SWAP64F(_i) (_i)
4241#define BE_SWAP32F(_i) (_i)
4242#define BE_SWAP32(_i) (_i)
4243#define BE_SWAP16(_i) (_i)
4244#define LE_SWAP64F(_i) flipDoubleCopy(_i)
4245#define LE_SWAP32F(_i) flipFloatCopy(_i)
4246#define LE_SWAP32(_i) (SWAP32(_i))
4247#define LE_SWAP16(_i) (SWAP16(_i))
4248#endif
